463
00:34:51,000 --> 00:34:54,000
The chance to herself over and over again.

464
00:34:54,000 --> 00:34:58,000
I want to look inside my pouch because that's where I had put Donnie.

465
00:34:58,000 --> 00:35:03,000
You look down and into your satchel and he stirs.

466
00:35:03,000 --> 00:35:06,000
I give his tummy a scratch.

467
00:35:06,000 --> 00:35:10,000
You follow Drazul who drops the sigil on his door.

468
00:35:10,000 --> 00:35:15,000
He leads you down some corridors and you begin to hear the sound of music.

469
00:35:15,000 --> 00:35:16,000
Soft.

470
00:35:16,000 --> 00:35:22,000
The closer you get, you find you're coming up to what looks like a worn down shop front,

471
00:35:22,000 --> 00:35:23,000
store front.

472
00:35:23,000 --> 00:35:27,000
Drazul is holding a torch that illuminates the sign.

473
00:35:27,000 --> 00:35:32,000
Previously had something scrawled into it, but now just over top in what looks like

474
00:35:32,000 --> 00:35:38,000
a deep red ink, maybe, says Noodle's shop.

475
00:35:38,000 --> 00:35:43,000
And inside Drazul calls out Noodle.

476
00:35:43,000 --> 00:35:48,000
Got some friends here and we need to see if you've got something.

477
00:35:48,000 --> 00:35:50,000
If you wouldn't mind.

478
00:35:50,000 --> 00:35:59,000
You hear a deep laughter come from deep within another room and out floats an old

479
00:35:59,000 --> 00:36:02,000
graying beholder.

480
00:36:03,000 --> 00:36:07,000
It's got hair coming out of pretty much everywhere.

481
00:36:07,000 --> 00:36:13,000
Not in like a fur fashion, but like old man hairs.

482
00:36:13,000 --> 00:36:14,000
Like wispy grays?

483
00:36:14,000 --> 00:36:15,000
Wispy grays.

484
00:36:15,000 --> 00:36:16,000
Okay.

485
00:36:16,000 --> 00:36:17,000
Like all over the place.

486
00:36:17,000 --> 00:36:18,000
I have a really good visual of this beholder.

487
00:36:18,000 --> 00:36:20,000
Yeah, me too and it is unsettling.

488
00:36:20,000 --> 00:36:23,000
A beholder is pretty gross anyway.

489
00:36:23,000 --> 00:36:24,000
But with hair?

490
00:36:24,000 --> 00:36:26,000
Now it's a hairy beholder.

491
00:36:26,000 --> 00:36:27,000
Gross.

492
00:36:27,000 --> 00:36:30,000
I look deep into this beholder's eye.

493
00:36:30,000 --> 00:36:35,000
All of the stalks turn towards you as you're looking in his eye.

494
00:36:35,000 --> 00:36:37,000
Do I know you?

495
00:36:37,000 --> 00:36:40,000
His entire body turns.

496
00:36:40,000 --> 00:36:42,000
No.

497
00:36:42,000 --> 00:36:43,000
Are you sure?

498
00:36:43,000 --> 00:36:45,000
How long have you had the name Noodle?

499
00:36:45,000 --> 00:36:47,000
Since I was created.

500
00:36:47,000 --> 00:36:51,000
Do you know who created you?

501
00:36:51,000 --> 00:36:53,000
He squints towards you.

502
00:36:53,000 --> 00:36:55,000
What do you want?

503
00:36:55,000 --> 00:36:57,000
Some rare ink, please.

504
00:36:57,000 --> 00:36:59,000
Drazul steps forward.

505
00:36:59,000 --> 00:37:00,000
Yeah.

506
00:37:00,000 --> 00:37:06,000
We need to create a teleportation spell and hands him the lists.

507
00:37:06,000 --> 00:37:09,000
Or just shows it to him rather.

508
00:37:09,000 --> 00:37:13,000
He looks at it and says, yeah, I might have it.

509
00:37:13,000 --> 00:37:17,000
It's going to run a pretty high tab though if you're trying to get out of town there.

510
00:37:17,000 --> 00:37:21,000
Drazul says, no, I'm not getting out of town.

511
00:37:21,000 --> 00:37:23,000
It's just for my friends here.

512
00:37:23,000 --> 00:37:26,000
What do you got for me?

513
00:37:26,000 --> 00:37:35,000
Well, do you want gold or what is your economy based on here in the tunnels?

514
00:37:35,000 --> 00:37:38,000
Well, it's generally what you got.

515
00:37:38,000 --> 00:37:39,000
I mean, if you got gold, that's great.

516
00:37:39,000 --> 00:37:41,000
If you got limbs, that's fine too.

517
00:37:41,000 --> 00:37:42,000
We could take that.

518
00:37:42,000 --> 00:37:43,000
I'm sorry.

519
00:37:43,000 --> 00:37:44,000
Did you say limbs?

520
00:37:44,000 --> 00:37:45,000
Yeah.

521
00:37:45,000 --> 00:37:48,000
Look, things have gotten a little, you know, the economy.

522
00:37:48,000 --> 00:37:50,000
What is money?

523
00:37:50,000 --> 00:37:52,000
What is money now that there's not many people down here?

524
00:37:52,000 --> 00:37:53,000
Food.

525
00:37:53,000 --> 00:37:54,000
Food is money.

526
00:37:54,000 --> 00:37:59,000
Ever since the noodle incident, really, anything goes.

527
00:37:59,000 --> 00:38:01,000
Cool.

528
00:38:01,000 --> 00:38:02,000
Okay.

529
00:38:02,000 --> 00:38:12,000
Well, on my person, I bring out a giant diamond.

530
00:38:12,000 --> 00:38:18,000
You feel it like pull in your hand?

531
00:38:18,000 --> 00:38:20,000
Oh, no, no, no, no, no, no.

532
00:38:20,000 --> 00:38:26,000
Well, I'd like to inspect the goods before I know exactly what we're working with here.

533
00:38:26,000 --> 00:38:33,000
Well, you have to be very careful with it because you might fuck it up.

534
00:38:33,000 --> 00:38:37,000
This is a very special teleportation diamond.

535
00:38:37,000 --> 00:38:40,000
Oh, if you got a teleportation diamond, what do you need ink for?

536
00:38:40,000 --> 00:38:44,000
It's not quite as far as I want to go.

537
00:38:44,000 --> 00:38:47,000
And look how pretty it is and how big.

538
00:38:47,000 --> 00:38:50,000
Very, very pretty and very big.

539
00:38:50,000 --> 00:38:51,000
Just let me look at it.

540
00:38:51,000 --> 00:38:55,000
I bring it closer, but I keep it well within my grasp.

541
00:38:55,000 --> 00:38:57,000
Looks nice.

542
00:38:57,000 --> 00:38:58,000
You need some ink?

543
00:38:58,000 --> 00:38:59,000
Mm-hmm.

544
00:38:59,000 --> 00:39:00,000
All right, give me a sec.

545
00:39:00,000 --> 00:39:01,000
Let me see what I got here.

546
00:39:01,000 --> 00:39:02,000
Purple, if you've got it.

547
00:39:02,000 --> 00:39:07,000
Stinking newbies bringing me in.

548
00:39:07,000 --> 00:39:15,000
Drizzle looks to you as he goes back and whispers, it was a lot more fun before, before all of this.

549
00:39:15,000 --> 00:39:18,000
I bet that could probably be said about a lot of you.

550
00:39:18,000 --> 00:39:19,000
Yeah, that's true.

551
00:39:19,000 --> 00:39:27,000
I mean, he went from selling like he was the joke shop owner up above to this, bartering for limbs.

552
00:39:27,000 --> 00:39:29,000
Oh.

553
00:39:29,000 --> 00:39:33,000
And are the limbs to eat or?

554
00:39:33,000 --> 00:39:34,000
Eat, trade.

555
00:39:34,000 --> 00:39:36,000
Let's trade.

556
00:39:36,000 --> 00:39:37,000
I do not understand.

557
00:39:37,000 --> 00:39:38,000
Trade for what?

558
00:39:38,000 --> 00:39:40,000
People lose arm, they need a new one?

559
00:39:40,000 --> 00:39:42,000
This is the kind of magic you can do now?

560
00:39:42,000 --> 00:39:44,000
Well, yeah, I mean, here and there.

561
00:39:44,000 --> 00:39:51,000
I mean, mostly it's food or components or sustenance.

562
00:39:51,000 --> 00:40:00,000
Trigger for, you know, throw it over there when we're trying to get somewhere, let some undead go for it.

563
00:40:00,000 --> 00:40:04,000
You all need to leave this place.

564
00:40:04,000 --> 00:40:07,000
We were just in the forest outside the city.

565
00:40:07,000 --> 00:40:10,000
It is not this.

566
00:40:10,000 --> 00:40:14,000
It is not undead and sand.

567
00:40:14,000 --> 00:40:16,000
It is as it was.

568
00:40:16,000 --> 00:40:17,000
No city, but.

569
00:40:17,000 --> 00:40:19,000
You could rebuild in the forest.

570
00:40:19,000 --> 00:40:20,000
Yeah.

571
00:40:20,000 --> 00:40:25,000
Trust me, when I say people live in the forest, I point to my ears.

572
00:40:25,000 --> 00:40:28,000
The forest has its dangers as well.

573
00:40:28,000 --> 00:40:31,000
It's the danger you're willing to accept, I guess.

574
00:40:31,000 --> 00:40:35,000
I know, but there's also like food in a forest.

575
00:40:35,000 --> 00:40:37,000
Yes, and the sun.

576
00:40:37,000 --> 00:40:39,000
And you're going to run out down here.

577
00:40:39,000 --> 00:40:42,000
You guys are all going to go mad down here.

578
00:40:42,000 --> 00:40:46,000
Yeah.

579
00:40:46,000 --> 00:40:47,000
That was unsettling.

580
00:40:47,000 --> 00:40:48,000
Noodle comes back.

581
00:40:48,000 --> 00:40:49,000
I got your ink.

582
00:40:49,000 --> 00:40:51,000
Here you go.

583
00:40:51,000 --> 00:40:52,000
He places it on the table.

584
00:40:52,000 --> 00:40:56,000
It floats down and rests on the table.

585
00:40:56,000 --> 00:40:58,000
Leave your diamond.

586
00:40:58,000 --> 00:40:59,000
I'm no noob.

587
00:40:59,000 --> 00:41:00,000
I put my diamond down.

588
00:41:00,000 --> 00:41:02,000
I keep my hand on it.

589
00:41:02,000 --> 00:41:04,000
I grasp the ink well.

590
00:41:04,000 --> 00:41:05,000
Do I feel it?

591
00:41:05,000 --> 00:41:06,000
It is corporeal.

592
00:41:06,000 --> 00:41:07,000
Yeah, it's corporeal.

593
00:41:07,000 --> 00:41:08,000
OK.

594
00:41:08,000 --> 00:41:09,000
You feel it?

595
00:41:09,000 --> 00:41:11,000
I like that you think you're going to get swindled.

596
00:41:11,000 --> 00:41:15,000
I do think that immediately any transactions happening in D&D, I'm like, this person's

597
00:41:15,000 --> 00:41:20,000
about to fuck me over now before I fuck them first.

598
00:41:20,000 --> 00:41:21,000
Very aggressive.

599
00:41:21,000 --> 00:41:23,000
I don't know why I have this distrust in me.

600
00:41:23,000 --> 00:41:25,000
I do not think this way in real life.

601
00:41:25,000 --> 00:41:31,000
Well, there's been multiple instances where we've had things not be as they appear

602
00:41:31,000 --> 00:41:33,000
thanks to our lovely dungeon masters.

603
00:41:33,000 --> 00:41:38,000
Sometimes we trust the wrong people, creatures, which is children.

604
00:41:38,000 --> 00:41:40,000
There's no children in this scene.

605
00:41:40,000 --> 00:41:47,000
I have my hand on the ink, and as I grasp the ink, I let go of the diamond.

606
00:41:47,000 --> 00:41:50,000
And I say, if you want to use it.

607
00:41:50,000 --> 00:41:52,000
Well, sorry, that's assuming you don't know how to use it.

608
00:41:52,000 --> 00:41:54,000
Would you like an explanation of how to use it?

609
00:41:54,000 --> 00:41:57,000
And I pass the ink well to Drzul.

610
00:41:57,000 --> 00:41:58,000
I'll figure it out.

611
00:41:58,000 --> 00:42:00,000
All right, but you only get one chance.

612
00:42:00,000 --> 00:42:01,000
Fair enough.

613
00:42:01,000 --> 00:42:02,000
Best of luck to you.

614
00:42:02,000 --> 00:42:04,000
Hey, what's your shop called?

615
00:42:04,000 --> 00:42:08,000
Like noodles, oodles of magic?

616
00:42:08,000 --> 00:42:09,000
You've been.

617
00:42:09,000 --> 00:42:12,000
No, but great name in.

618
00:42:12,000 --> 00:42:13,000
Thanks.

619
00:42:13,000 --> 00:42:14,000
Hey, don't lose your spark, man.

620
00:42:14,000 --> 00:42:15,000
I'll do what I can.

621
00:42:15,000 --> 00:42:17,000
Better hurry along.

622
00:42:17,000 --> 00:42:18,000
Why?

623
00:42:18,000 --> 00:42:19,000
What's going to happen to that ink?

624
00:42:19,000 --> 00:42:20,000
Nothing.

625
00:42:20,000 --> 00:42:21,000
Okay.

626
00:42:21,000 --> 00:42:23,000
Be safe, Drzul.

627
00:42:23,000 --> 00:42:26,000
Drzul begins to walk out of the shop, leading you out.

628
00:42:26,000 --> 00:42:27,000
I guess.

629
00:42:27,000 --> 00:42:29,000
That was a weird transaction.

630
00:42:30,000 --> 00:42:31,000
Yep.

631
00:42:31,000 --> 00:42:33,000
It's all unsettling down here.

632
00:42:33,000 --> 00:42:34,000
Very much is.

633
00:42:34,000 --> 00:42:40,000
There's just a cackle of laughter coming from the shop mixed in with the music as

634
00:42:40,000 --> 00:42:43,000
you begin to walk back down.

635
00:42:43,000 --> 00:42:46,000
Drzul turns and says, we should probably go quickly.

636
00:42:46,000 --> 00:42:47,000
Okay.

637
00:42:47,000 --> 00:42:48,000
Yes.

638
00:42:48,000 --> 00:42:49,000
Okay.

639
00:42:49,000 --> 00:42:50,000
Yes.

640
00:42:50,000 --> 00:42:53,000
He leads you back down the corridors and back to his home.

641
00:42:53,000 --> 00:42:58,000
And you hear high pitched laughter coming from down the halls.

642
00:42:58,000 --> 00:43:04,000
He opens the door and closes it and puts up the sigil.

643
00:43:04,000 --> 00:43:11,000
And as it activates, you hear a loud thud and an explosion out on the other side of

644
00:43:11,000 --> 00:43:12,000
the door.

645
00:43:12,000 --> 00:43:13,000
Was that Noodle?

646
00:43:13,000 --> 00:43:15,000
No, probably his thugs.

647
00:43:15,000 --> 00:43:20,000
This only holds for a few more hits though, so we should probably get you going.

648
00:43:20,000 --> 00:43:21,000
Yes.

649
00:43:21,000 --> 00:43:26,000
What about, uh, you come with us?

650
00:43:26,000 --> 00:43:32,000
You go to the city, you learn how to defeat undead, you come back, you save everyone.

651
00:43:32,000 --> 00:43:34,000
That sounds nice.

652
00:43:34,000 --> 00:43:36,000
Another explosion goes.

653
00:43:36,000 --> 00:43:40,000
Um, I'll get started here.

654
00:43:40,000 --> 00:43:44,000
He goes over to his spell book.

655
00:43:44,000 --> 00:43:48,000
You can see through like the cracks in the door, there's small figures on the

656
00:43:48,000 --> 00:43:52,000
other side moving back and forth, pacing in front of the door and there's like

657
00:43:52,000 --> 00:43:54,000
mumbled chatter.

658
00:43:54,000 --> 00:43:58,000
You can't quite make out what they're saying because of the sigil, but it

659
00:43:58,000 --> 00:43:59,000
sounds like they're arguing.

660
00:43:59,000 --> 00:44:02,000
And then it sounds like there's hands like hitting together.

661
00:44:02,000 --> 00:44:09,000
There's a little rock paper scissors happening on the other side.

662
00:44:09,000 --> 00:44:12,000
Another explosion goes after a few minutes.

663
00:44:12,000 --> 00:44:16,000
The sigil, does it just stop things from coming in or would it stop

664
00:44:16,000 --> 00:44:18,000
something from going out?

665
00:44:18,000 --> 00:44:21,000
It prevents movement from either side.

666
00:44:21,000 --> 00:44:23,000
Well, that's less than helpful.

667
00:44:23,000 --> 00:44:24,000
Never mind.

668
00:44:24,000 --> 00:44:25,000
Okay.

669
00:44:25,000 --> 00:44:28,000
He goes back to prepping the room.

670
00:44:28,000 --> 00:44:33,000
Drazul turns to you and says, okay, I think, I think we're ready.

671
00:44:33,000 --> 00:44:35,000
If you just cluster together there.

672
00:44:35,000 --> 00:44:38,000
Yen Bol, are you coming?

673
00:44:38,000 --> 00:44:43,000
Yes, I, I, I can't fight everything here.

674
00:44:43,000 --> 00:44:47,000
I must get stronger or get allies.

675
00:44:47,000 --> 00:44:52,000
Don't know where this is going to bring you up in Waterdeep, but, um,

676
00:44:52,000 --> 00:44:53,000
best of luck.

677
00:44:53,000 --> 00:44:56,000
I hope it's not in between a wall.

678
00:44:56,000 --> 00:44:57,000
What?

679
00:44:57,000 --> 00:45:01,000
He begins moving his hands in the air.

680
00:45:01,000 --> 00:45:05,000
Lenergy begins to glow on this, on the sigil.

681
00:45:05,000 --> 00:45:11,000
He's traced and written out in the chalk and ink on the ground.

682
00:45:11,000 --> 00:45:13,000
Says, I'll see you.

683
00:45:13,000 --> 00:45:19,000
The light around you shoots up and you, the room begins to fade as you hear

684
00:45:19,000 --> 00:45:23,000
another explosion from the door.

685
00:45:23,000 --> 00:45:27,000
It flickers in and out of your vision.

686
00:45:27,000 --> 00:45:32,000
The room that you were in and the street in Waterdeep.

687
00:45:32,000 --> 00:45:38,000
You're in an alleyway, flicks back and forth and you see the door break open

688
00:45:38,000 --> 00:45:48,000
as three thugs begin to rush into the room and grab at Drazul.

689
00:45:48,000 --> 00:45:51,000
And then you're in an alleyway in Waterdeep.

690
00:45:51,000 --> 00:45:56,000
You look around, you see people walking down on the main road.

691
00:45:56,000 --> 00:46:03,000
Flint, you feel like a super sharp pang in your head.

692
00:46:03,000 --> 00:46:08,000
We gotta, we gotta hustle here, peeps.

693
00:46:08,000 --> 00:46:11,000
You definitely look like you're in hustling form.

694
00:46:11,000 --> 00:46:16,000
And I look around for a cart or a carriage or something to flag down

695
00:46:16,000 --> 00:46:20,000
to get us quickly to the people I need to see.

696
00:46:20,000 --> 00:46:23,000
You're bracing Flint as you walk down towards the main road

697
00:46:23,000 --> 00:46:29,000
and as you step out into the main road, you look up

698
00:46:29,000 --> 00:46:39,000
and immediately what catches your eye are dark black banners hanging from the streets.

699
00:46:39,000 --> 00:46:48,000
With the symbol of orcas along all of them.

700
00:46:48,000 --> 00:46:53,000
You look at the people and they're quickly rushing about from place to place.

701
00:46:53,000 --> 00:46:56,000
Some of them looking at the sun.

702
00:46:56,000 --> 00:47:02,000
A lot of doors are shutting up as you realize it's getting towards sundown.

